[SN]TITLE[SN]
Craig Greve admits owning dog which killed his grandmother

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has admitted owning a dog which fatally attacked his grandmother at their Cardiff home.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Rhona Greve, 64, died after suffering neck and face injuries when she was bitten 16 times by Craig Greve's American bulldog, Solo, on 20 March.
Greve, 23, of Ely, admitted being the owner of a dog which was dangerously out of control at Cardiff Crown Court.
He was remanded in custody until his sentencing in September.
